1
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:17,350
How did you get hurt so badly?

2
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:19,470
What is the situation?

3
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:21,550
Met someone useless.

4
00:00:22,270 --> 00:00:24,180
Mo Yungao didn't show up at all.

5
00:00:24,330 --> 00:00:25,640
But just as I guessed,

6
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:27,760
they have already made their move.

7
00:00:28,910 --> 00:00:31,040
That group is trickier than I thought.

8
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:56,600
They already know I am Miss Dong.

9
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,330
They might attack
the Dong Residence right away.

10
00:01:06,140 --> 00:01:08,840
I missed you so much,

11
00:01:09,180 --> 00:01:11,050
Miss Dong.

12
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,410
You are not Mo Yungao.

13
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,560
Take everyone in the Dong family

14
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,150
and leave Xiacheng now.

15
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:20,880
It's best to leave the country.

16
00:01:21,390 --> 00:01:22,720
This is the concession.

17
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:24,740
No one dares to make a move here.

18
00:01:24,940 --> 00:01:25,940
Besides,

19
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:28,000
you are the daughter
of the Ship King.

20
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:28,930
In Xiacheng,

21
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:31,850
no one can touch you.

22
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,920
If a gun is fired here,

23
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:38,160
friends from other consulates
will send troops.

24
00:01:38,789 --> 00:01:40,789
Rest and recover with peace of mind.

25
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:42,890
It's different this time.

26
00:01:43,229 --> 00:01:45,090
This time we are facing a warlord.

27
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,259
That Lu Junxiang, too—

28
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,660
he will definitely try
every possible means to kill me.

29
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:51,740
Lu Junxiang?

30
00:01:52,450 --> 00:01:54,910
A prisoner captured
at the Archives before.

31
00:01:58,720 --> 00:01:59,380
No.

32
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:02,910
You must leave immediately.

33
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:10,000
I won't leave you behind.

34
00:02:14,450 --> 00:02:15,330
Mr. Dong.

35
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:17,360
I was just using you.

36
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,800
Back then,
I needed this identity to protect myself.

37
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,060
There's not much time left
for you to run.

38
00:02:31,220 --> 00:02:33,350
I didn't expect him to come so quickly.

39
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:35,630
I really underestimated him.

40
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:15,340
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

41
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:18,339
[Episode 13]

42
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:27,810
Why is there nothing?

43
00:04:30,890 --> 00:04:34,530
[Six hours left]

44
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:37,480
Plague.

45
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:38,810
Plague?

46
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:40,990
Plague!

47
00:04:41,409 --> 00:04:42,560
I finally found you.

48
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,120
Why are you here?

49
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,510
Do you know how hard I looked for you?

50
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:45,920
I have something important to tell you.

51
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,800
Whatever you're saying right now,

52
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:47,600
I can't hear it.

53
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,430
I have something very important
to do right now.

54
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:51,010
-Hey.
-Time is running out.

55
00:04:51,010 --> 00:04:52,159
I-I know.

56
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:53,760
I have something to give you.

57
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:54,860
Money!

58
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,250
Listen to me!

59
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,430
It's money!

60
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:58,659
Your friend—

61
00:04:58,659 --> 00:04:59,430
Get lost.

62
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:03,420
Zhang Hailou!

63
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,930
I don't care what you're doing.

64
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,290
What could be so important

65
00:05:07,290 --> 00:05:10,890
that it's more important
than what your dead friend left behind?

66
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:13,750
These are the things your friend

67
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,780
asked me to give you before he died.

68
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,190
I guess there's very important information
on this,

69
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:20,250
which is why I turned back to find you.

70
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,100
You keep it.

71
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:25,550
This is Shrimpie's money.

72
00:05:27,050 --> 00:05:28,340
I don't know who he is.

73
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:31,560
Anyway, your friend asked me
to give it to you.

74
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:32,750
Why do you have it?

75
00:05:32,970 --> 00:05:34,290
It was on the ship.

76
00:05:34,659 --> 00:05:36,600
Your friend slipped it to me

77
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,830
in a very chaotic situation.

78
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,240
He told me to give it to his partner.

79
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,370
How was I supposed to know that was you?

80
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,810
But whatever happened in between,

81
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:43,570
I have no idea.

82
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:44,770
Anyway, by coincidence,

83
00:05:44,770 --> 00:05:46,210
things have come to this.

84
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:47,920
There must be some

85
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,420
important hidden information on it.

86
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:50,620
That's why I came back

87
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:52,080
to find you in such a hurry.

88
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:56,909
You...

89
00:05:57,380 --> 00:05:59,640
Why didn't I keep an eye on him
on the ship?

90
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,420
All right.

91
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:02,890
Hurry up and see

92
00:06:02,890 --> 00:06:05,420
if there's anything important
on this money.

93
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,020
Two-square cipher.

94
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:17,780
Is this a military decryption method?

95
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,690
As long as you have
the key and the ciphertext,

96
00:06:19,690 --> 00:06:21,490
you can decipher the words on it.

97
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:25,870
You know about this?

98
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,560
I don't.

99
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,930
It's you—you're a lucky guy.

100
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,880
God is watching over you.

101
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:34,670
When I was looking for you,

102
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:36,060
I ran into a bunch of robbers.

103
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,620
I almost died there.

104
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,020
Patrolman!

105
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,000
Right here!

106
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:43,070
Someone is committing robbery here!

107
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:44,040
Take it, take it.

108
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:46,430
Luckily, I met a kind-hearted person.

109
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:47,250
She saved me.

110
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:56,970
[Wesley, Haili Bank Manager]

111
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,810
She is the manager of Haili Bank.

112
00:06:55,810 --> 00:06:57,480
Her father was a foreign soldier.

113
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,980
That's how I know all this.

114
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,250
The code on this money

115
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:02,000
should be a two-square cipher.

116
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,980
Generally, only people
in special military and political work

117
00:07:04,980 --> 00:07:05,680
would use it.

118
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,560
It's mainly used
to transmit important intelligence.

119
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:10,280
[Haili Bank]

120
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:10,230
It was also her
who mobilized everyone in Haili Bank

121
00:07:10,230 --> 00:07:11,290
to help me find you.

122
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:13,080
Call everyone out here.

123
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:13,930
Help me find someone.

124
00:07:13,930 --> 00:07:14,590
President.

125
00:07:14,930 --> 00:07:15,540
Come over.

126
00:07:16,230 --> 00:07:16,690
Quick.

127
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,080
President.

128
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,050
Found him.

129
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:21,790
It's him.

130
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,620
It's him. It definitely is him.

131
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,540
[Missing Person]

132
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:29,440
[Discussing the past
and lamenting the present]

133
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:26,210
He was here
listening to stories during the day.

134
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:28,010
When he heard us talk about
the temple of the underworld by the sea,

135
00:07:28,010 --> 00:07:29,410
he ran away immediately.

136
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:30,400
Take a look.

137
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,870
Do these characters on it

138
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:35,480
spell out the word...

139
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:36,920
Plan—

140
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,250
a set of decisions.

141
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:38,780
Plot—

142
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,530
conspiracy.

143
00:07:39,659 --> 00:07:40,130
Fake—

144
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:40,690
disguise.

145
00:07:40,690 --> 00:07:41,120
ASAP—

146
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,250
as soon as possible.

147
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:53,330
This is a plot.

148
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:55,390
I have a plan.

149
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:57,950
I need to fake something.

150
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:58,950
Come save me ASAP.

151
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,660
Isn't your friend dead?

152
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:03,050
Why would he s-say "ASAP"?

153
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,300
He faked his death.

154
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:05,910
Faked his death?

155
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:09,200
There should be a way
to save him on these bills.

156
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:09,790
Then...

157
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:11,100
That's a lot of bills—

158
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,800
how do you know which bill it is?

159
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,080
During our training,

160
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,990
we also used money for codes.

161
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,660
We'd look at the serial numbers

162
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,070
and arrange the bills in order.

163
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,090
I get it.

164
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:22,460
I have this habit too when keeping books.

165
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:25,120
I like to arrange bills
by their serial numbers.

166
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,810
You're a natural-born spy.

167
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:35,159
Danan Telegraph Office.

168
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:36,929
So it's Haili Bank.

169
00:08:37,289 --> 00:08:37,960
Cracks.

170
00:08:38,970 --> 00:08:39,750
Eye.

171
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:41,220
Wait.

172
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:42,400
Haili Bank?

173
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:44,670
Cracks, eyes—what do those mean?

174
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:45,890
Haili Bank...

175
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:47,290
The Southern Archives

176
00:08:47,290 --> 00:08:48,810
has an outer defense mechanism

177
00:08:48,810 --> 00:08:50,140
right below Haili Bank.

178
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,550
The Southern Archives?

179
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:56,300
God is indeed looking out for me.

180
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,630
Thank you, Cousin.

181
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,700
For everything I owe you,

182
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:03,560
I'll pay you back in the next life.

183
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:09,500
Haili Bank.

184
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,650
Plague, wait for me!

185
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:35,520
Mr. Warner.

186
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:39,010
The 3 miles around the Dong Mansion

187
00:09:39,010 --> 00:09:41,460
have been completely cleared.

188
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:44,260
And there's a whole army out there
surrounding it.

189
00:09:45,370 --> 00:09:47,520
We can't stay any longer
in this mess.

190
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:49,410
Pick up the men, we have to leave.

191
00:09:49,410 --> 00:09:50,010
All right.

192
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:51,530
Mr. Warner,

193
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:54,220
our deal hasn't been finalized yet.

194
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,060
You're leaving?

195
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,530
Aren't you after the treasure on the map?

196
00:09:58,980 --> 00:09:59,740
Miss Dong,

197
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:02,720
you should be very clear
about the situation outside.

198
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,920
It's very dangerous.

199
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,220
Those treasures

200
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:06,530
are not worth dying

201
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:07,920
in a foreign land.

202
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:09,220
Miss Dong,

203
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:11,100
your enemy will not stop

204
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:13,510
until you are dead.

205
00:10:15,170 --> 00:10:17,200
If my musketeers withdraw now,

206
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,790
maybe everyone

207
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:19,990
will be slaughtered.

208
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:25,980
Come in.

209
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:49,010
Move it.

210
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,460
And I'll show you real wealth.

211
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,570
What's exactly below here?

212
00:11:20,460 --> 00:11:21,720
It's just

213
00:11:22,210 --> 00:11:23,930
a vault of the Dong family.

214
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,030
I've changed my mind.

215
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:28,810
We are going to protect Miss Dong.

216
00:11:28,810 --> 00:11:29,770
Miss Dong,

217
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:31,860
you will keep your promise, right?

218
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:32,580
Of course.

219
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:35,800
They have a thousand times
more troops than we do.

220
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:38,500
We go head-on, we dead.

221
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,390
Since your boss agreed,

222
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,140
it means he knows we will win.

223
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:43,520
My friends, we will win!

224
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:44,480
With our treasure,

225
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,270
with our guns—

226
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:46,070
huh!

227
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,280
Come on!

228
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:03,510
Prepare to attack.

229
00:12:03,540 --> 00:12:04,000
Yes!

230
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:02,000
Who the hell is this Miss Dong?

231
00:13:02,030 --> 00:13:04,780
She even knows
how to deploy troops and fire.

232
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:07,170
Those are some

233
00:13:07,170 --> 00:13:07,910
tricky shooting points

234
00:13:07,910 --> 00:13:08,510
she worked out.

235
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:10,780
The hardest part is dealing
against the enemy.

236
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:12,700
No, it's because of Maxim gun!

237
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:31,710
I wonder where
the consulate people are now.

238
00:13:32,490 --> 00:13:33,850
Can they hold out?

239
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:45,130
Ammunition loaded.

240
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,000
Fire!

241
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:50,000
Stand back!

242
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,050
Fire!

243
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,640
Stand back!

244
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,300
Hurry up! Hurry up!

245
00:14:22,810 --> 00:14:25,460
[Haili Bank]

246
00:15:10,430 --> 00:15:10,890
Cousin.

247
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,310
Why...

248
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,860
Why are you here again?
Stop following me.

249
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:13,260
You...

250
00:15:15,630 --> 00:15:16,200
If you dare call for help,

251
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,660
I'll burn this place down.

252
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:19,560
You know I'm capable of anything.

253
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:24,310
Okay, I won't shout.

254
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:25,460
But...

255
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,820
You have to let me watch you.

256
00:15:26,820 --> 00:15:28,880
I'm going into the Archives with you.

257
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:07,360
What are you doing?

258
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,890
I should be asking you that.

259
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,560
Mrs. Wesley, the manager of Haley Bank,

260
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:13,070
is your great benefactor.

261
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:14,730
If it wasn't for her help,

262
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:17,100
you wouldn't have gotten
your friend's belongings.

263
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,770
It's one thing not to repay her,

264
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:19,790
but we shouldn't
bite the hand that feeds us

265
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,050
and ruin her business.

266
00:16:27,010 --> 00:16:31,900
[Cracks] [Eyes]
[Chop (Cigarette brand)] [TB (Telegram)]

267
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:38,980
I'm sorry.

268
00:16:43,350 --> 00:16:45,010
I sincerely apologize to you.

269
00:16:45,410 --> 00:16:46,470
I really shouldn't

270
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,940
casually destroy
someone else's property.

271
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:54,550
At least you have a conscience.

272
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,270
You know me best.

273
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:01,460
Trying to choke me unconscious
and ditch me again?

274
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:02,300
No way.

275
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:05,150
I've been practicing in secret
for a long time.

276
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,730
Look closely for clues
about the cracks and the cigarettes.

277
00:18:27,490 --> 00:18:29,820
Don't... you have cigarettes right here?

278
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:32,950
Could the cigarettes he mentioned

279
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:35,700
mean something like a non-smoking area?

280
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:37,330
I'm just guessing.

281
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,340
Could the cigarettes
refer to the one in my hand?

282
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,490
Looks like the vent is here.

283
00:19:51,770 --> 00:19:53,710
You knew I couldn't quit smoking.

284
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,630
Here you are, still mocking me.

285
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:07,520
No.

286
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:11,390
Hey!

287
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:18,200
There's a smell.

288
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,560
What smell?

289
00:20:23,950 --> 00:20:24,760
Hard to say.

290
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:37,090
[Double Cloud]

291
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,030
Could this be the Southern Archives'

292
00:20:36,030 --> 00:20:37,690
defense mechanism entrance?

293
00:20:38,030 --> 00:20:40,360
Then what does the "eyes"
on the coin mean?

294
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:57,270
There's indeed something wrong
with this crack.

295
00:21:04,710 --> 00:21:05,800
Be careful.

296
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,290
Careful.

297
00:21:12,330 --> 00:21:13,390
What is this?

298
00:21:14,810 --> 00:21:15,540
Hard to tell.

299
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,060
This belongs to Haili Bank.

300
00:21:18,090 --> 00:21:18,820
Give it to me.

301
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:20,610
Give it.

302
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:21,530
Hey!

303
00:21:23,940 --> 00:21:24,940
I'm warning you.

304
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:27,130
When I go in later,

305
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,540
stop following me.

306
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:29,860
I can't protect you.

307
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:31,650
I got it.

308
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:33,150
You go first, or me?

309
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:34,590
Forget it, I'll go first.

310
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:52,870
Wait for me!

311
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:55,200
Slow... Slow down!

312
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,050
Wait for me!

313
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,630
Slow down!

314
00:22:08,810 --> 00:22:10,280
You're really very lucky.

315
00:22:10,660 --> 00:22:11,530
There's a door here.

316
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:12,350
It should be the exit.

317
00:22:12,350 --> 00:22:13,190
A door?

318
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:15,140
We're finally here.

319
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:15,600
Look.

320
00:22:16,330 --> 00:22:17,080
Right here.

321
00:22:17,430 --> 00:22:18,330
Let me see.

322
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:23,460
Where is the door?

323
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:27,160
Where?

324
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:28,640
The door retreated.

325
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:30,510
Retreated?

326
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:33,840
What do you mean? I don't get it.

327
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:34,790
When I was saw it,

328
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:35,980
there was a door right here.

329
00:22:35,980 --> 00:22:36,680
But as soon as I turned my head,

330
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,610
the door disappeared and ran away.

331
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,380
You're terrible at lying now.

332
00:22:45,410 --> 00:22:46,330
I might not be smart,

333
00:22:46,330 --> 00:22:47,700
but I'm not stupid.

334
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:49,550
Stop trying to fool me.

335
00:22:49,550 --> 00:22:50,550
I'm not leaving.

336
00:22:50,550 --> 00:22:51,660
I already told you.

337
00:22:52,370 --> 00:22:53,550
Wait for me.

338
00:22:56,460 --> 00:22:56,870
Look,

339
00:22:57,510 --> 00:22:59,040
there really is a door here.

340
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:00,450
This is it.

341
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:01,570
Door...

342
00:23:02,940 --> 00:23:03,810
my foot!

343
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:06,720
Can you stop messing with me?

344
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,940
There was definitely a door here just now.

345
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:09,050
A white jade door,

346
00:23:09,050 --> 00:23:10,010
carved with patterns.

347
00:23:10,010 --> 00:23:11,780
But as soon as you came, it ran away.

348
00:23:11,780 --> 00:23:12,670
Alright.

349
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:18,300
I got it.

350
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,940
There's something wrong with your face.

351
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:22,350
Every time I look back at your face

352
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:24,210
and turn around, the door is gone.

353
00:23:24,340 --> 00:23:25,400
Or maybe this door

354
00:23:25,610 --> 00:23:27,410
needs to be watched all the time.

355
00:23:28,070 --> 00:23:29,360
Seriously?

356
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:30,780
That's a personal attack.

357
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:32,900
You're the one
with something wrong with your face.

358
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:35,720
Plague, slow down! Wait for me!

359
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:38,350
Go.

360
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:39,310
Hurry up.

361
00:23:41,470 --> 00:23:42,470
I see the door.

362
00:23:43,990 --> 00:23:44,560
Quick.

363
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:46,680
Hold the flashlight for me.

364
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:56,110
There really is a door.

365
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:57,740
What should we do?

366
00:23:57,930 --> 00:23:59,260
Is it because I blinked?

367
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:02,830
Look.

368
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:06,790
Wait, wait, wait.

369
00:24:06,790 --> 00:24:07,990
Let me think about it.

370
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:11,990
[Eyes]

371
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,790
I think I know the secret to this thing.

372
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,780
It needs us

373
00:24:17,070 --> 00:24:18,500
to keep staring at it

374
00:24:18,530 --> 00:24:19,330
without blinking ever

375
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:20,130
to capture it.

376
00:24:20,270 --> 00:24:20,850
Cousin.

377
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:22,110
Don't worry. Leave it to me.

378
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:22,910
I'll open the door.

379
00:24:22,910 --> 00:24:23,650
Wait.

380
00:24:25,550 --> 00:24:27,040
Let me try.

381
00:24:28,190 --> 00:24:28,930
Can you do it?

382
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:48,860
Still there, still there, still there.

383
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:50,260
You didn't blink, right?

384
00:24:50,340 --> 00:24:51,210
I didn't.

385
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:52,310
I got it.

386
00:25:14,610 --> 00:25:16,780
There's a draft through the door.

387
00:25:38,290 --> 00:25:39,890
Plague, Plague, Plague.

388
00:25:41,460 --> 00:25:42,900
Come, come, come!

389
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:45,440
I'm coming!

390
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:52,010
You smashed my hand!

391
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:52,680
I...

392
00:26:37,410 --> 00:26:39,210
Are you trying to kill yourself?

393
00:26:41,530 --> 00:26:42,360
Are you okay?

394
00:26:44,430 --> 00:26:45,410
I'm fine.

395
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:47,630
Looks like we found the Archives.

396
00:26:48,650 --> 00:26:49,380
Get up.

397
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:53,380
They're in the yard already.

398
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,770
The machine guns in the secret passage

399
00:26:54,770 --> 00:26:56,060
have all been set up.

400
00:26:56,090 --> 00:26:57,960
Even if the consulate's reinforcements
don't arrive,

401
00:26:57,960 --> 00:26:59,150
as long as they enter the passage,

402
00:26:59,150 --> 00:27:00,110
within half an hour,

403
00:27:00,110 --> 00:27:01,740
I can kill them all.

404
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:03,380
What's the situation out there?

405
00:27:03,380 --> 00:27:04,510
Three of our men died.

406
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:06,420
Thirty-seven servants have been resettled.

407
00:27:06,420 --> 00:27:08,180
Two of them inhaled a poison gas,

408
00:27:08,180 --> 00:27:09,840
and they aren't looking good.

409
00:27:10,060 --> 00:27:11,180
Thirty-seven?

410
00:27:11,390 --> 00:27:14,050
Doesn't the Dong Mansion
only have 36 servants?

411
00:27:31,740 --> 00:27:34,360
Tell everyone
to enter that secret basement

412
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:35,970
and stay on alert.

413
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:43,510
Be careful!

414
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:34,390
My daughter...

415
00:28:34,420 --> 00:28:35,350
Don't talk.

416
00:28:35,820 --> 00:28:38,620
I'll find someone
to stop your bleeding right now.

417
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:42,150
You'll be on your own from now on.

418
00:28:44,010 --> 00:28:46,140
You must take good care of yourself.

419
00:28:47,140 --> 00:28:50,390
You have to live well.

420
00:29:26,740 --> 00:29:28,520
I have lived for way too long.

421
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:43,750
Into the tunnel.

422
00:30:42,670 --> 00:30:43,950
Tear down

423
00:30:44,830 --> 00:30:46,580
this entire room.

424
00:30:48,130 --> 00:30:50,400
Don't leave a single piece
of the wall intact.

425
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,060
-Yes!
-Yes!

426
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:56,440
Plague!

427
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:57,960
Wait for me!

428
00:30:58,570 --> 00:30:59,570
Hurry up, Cousin.

429
00:31:00,570 --> 00:31:01,770
Weren't you pretty strong just now?

430
00:31:01,770 --> 00:31:03,030
You even saved my life.

431
00:31:03,220 --> 00:31:04,020
Your reaction speed

432
00:31:04,020 --> 00:31:05,760
is much faster than before.

433
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:09,360
I still have a conscience,

434
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:10,660
unlike you

435
00:31:11,410 --> 00:31:12,540
who's so heartless.

436
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:14,810
Let's take a break.

437
00:31:18,150 --> 00:31:19,750
Now I just need to follow these clues

438
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:21,150
to find what I want.

439
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,430
Sure, sure.

440
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:25,440
Let's find it
and get out of here as soon as possible.

441
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:25,970
Let's go.

442
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,710
Is this the entrance?

443
00:32:14,930 --> 00:32:17,390
This is the only door
at the end of the tunnel.

444
00:32:24,420 --> 00:32:26,200
It's locked. We need a key.

445
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:27,830
Let's not look for the key.

446
00:32:27,830 --> 00:32:29,890
Why don't we just force the door open?

447
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:33,080
I smell sulfur.

448
00:32:33,950 --> 00:32:35,610
There are explosives inside.

449
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:37,730
It's true.

450
00:32:38,350 --> 00:32:39,440
If someone tries to pry the door open

451
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,560
or blow it up with explosives,

452
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,220
they'd be blown to pieces too.

453
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,280
We still need to find the key.

454
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:49,010
Where do we find it?

455
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:56,870
Anything?

456
00:32:59,270 --> 00:33:00,370
Inside here

457
00:33:01,070 --> 00:33:02,470
are fragments of the key.

458
00:33:08,620 --> 00:33:10,620
There are key fragments in here too.

459
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:12,400
They look a lot like yours.

460
00:33:13,970 --> 00:33:15,570
Are they in every single one?

461
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:17,280
My God.

462
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:18,760
There are so many.

463
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,190
You can't even tell the fragments apart.

464
00:33:21,190 --> 00:33:23,130
Isn't this to keep people out on purpose?

465
00:33:23,130 --> 00:33:25,070
This is the secret entrance
to the Archives.

466
00:33:25,070 --> 00:33:27,200
How could they let people in so easily?

467
00:33:27,380 --> 00:33:28,050
True.

468
00:33:29,530 --> 00:33:31,370
Look at the bills from your friend.

469
00:33:31,370 --> 00:33:33,400
There seem to be many symbol clues on it

470
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,500
that we haven't used yet.

471
00:33:34,500 --> 00:33:35,260
No need.

472
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,880
I've already figured it out.

473
00:33:42,950 --> 00:33:44,190
Are you sure?

474
00:33:44,470 --> 00:33:47,000
There are thousands of
possible arrangements for these fragments.

475
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,970
How long will it take you to solve it?

476
00:33:48,970 --> 00:33:49,900
Clam down.

477
00:33:53,300 --> 00:33:54,990
What would Shrimpie do?

478
00:33:58,740 --> 00:34:00,070
This is a dead end.

479
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:01,940
This is a scam.

480
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:03,440
I doubt Southern Archives

481
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,610
is here at all.

482
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:09,400
I got it.

483
00:34:11,409 --> 00:34:12,210
It's the plot.

484
00:34:21,210 --> 00:34:22,420
How is it?

485
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:23,929
Have you figured it out?

486
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:27,000
Any of the keys can open both locks.

487
00:34:36,850 --> 00:34:38,650
Mentor, I think this test is a bit...

488
00:34:38,650 --> 00:34:39,610
not worth it.

489
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:40,760
You only have two disciples.

490
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,100
One of us will end up disabled.

491
00:34:42,100 --> 00:34:43,360
If we are disabled,

492
00:34:43,650 --> 00:34:44,440
you have no one left to torture.

493
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,800
You two aren't that important.

494
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:46,610
I don't care.

495
00:34:46,830 --> 00:34:47,310
I...

496
00:34:49,929 --> 00:34:51,659
Shrimpie is pretty important.

497
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:52,960
I think this game

498
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:54,420
isn't a test of skill at all.

499
00:34:54,420 --> 00:34:56,010
It's about who has a tougher life.

500
00:34:56,010 --> 00:34:57,650
There's no need to deceive our feelings.

501
00:34:57,650 --> 00:34:58,150
Right?

502
00:34:58,610 --> 00:34:59,920
Mentor, I got it.

503
00:35:00,210 --> 00:35:02,010
You just want us to make a choice.

504
00:35:02,170 --> 00:35:02,670
Right.

505
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,230
But

506
00:35:07,460 --> 00:35:08,420
the time you have to choose is limited.

507
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:08,940
Mentor!

508
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:12,940
Is Mentor dating someone recently?

509
00:35:12,940 --> 00:35:15,470
Why is she getting
more and more mischievous?

510
00:35:19,810 --> 00:35:20,870
What are you doing?

511
00:35:21,050 --> 00:35:21,630
I'm fast.

512
00:35:21,630 --> 00:35:22,360
I can get the key.

513
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:23,890
Your hand will be crippled!

514
00:35:26,140 --> 00:35:26,840
I get it.

515
00:35:28,270 --> 00:35:29,120
It's a plot.

516
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:39,090
Run!

517
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,610
When you face a dilemma in the future,

518
00:35:51,610 --> 00:35:53,100
step back and think about it first.

519
00:35:53,100 --> 00:35:53,840
See if you

520
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:56,170
have already fallen into someone's plot.

521
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,640
It's just a mind trap.

522
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:01,950
There's an obvious man-made dilemma.

523
00:36:02,570 --> 00:36:04,410
Cousin, look at that door.

524
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:06,290
It looks like a door on the surface,

525
00:36:06,290 --> 00:36:07,620
but it actually isn't.

526
00:36:07,690 --> 00:36:08,360
Or rather,

527
00:36:08,420 --> 00:36:10,280
it doesn't want to let you in at all.

528
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:12,280
Normal people would stand in front
of the Bronze Ball Mechanism

529
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:13,630
and think for weeks.

530
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:15,940
But in actuality,

531
00:36:16,860 --> 00:36:18,400
it isn't an entrance at all.

532
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:21,230
But these puzzles make people feel

533
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:22,580
that if they think a little longer,

534
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:24,240
they can find the real answer.

535
00:36:24,450 --> 00:36:25,800
So they get trapped here.

536
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:27,280
When people think
in one place for too long,

537
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,610
they easily sink into it

538
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:29,870
and find it hard to change course.

539
00:36:29,870 --> 00:36:31,410
Only a very few geniuses

540
00:36:32,070 --> 00:36:33,270
can think in reverse.

541
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:35,180
Like me, for instance.

542
00:36:35,630 --> 00:36:36,530
So?

543
00:36:37,510 --> 00:36:38,280
So, cousin,

544
00:36:39,830 --> 00:36:41,430
we should search in reverse.

545
00:36:42,290 --> 00:36:43,060
Reverse?

546
00:36:44,500 --> 00:36:45,780
We're going back?

547
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,050
Are you crazy?

548
00:36:48,450 --> 00:36:49,300
Plague!

549
00:36:49,330 --> 00:36:51,440
I just got bandaged!

550
00:36:56,820 --> 00:36:57,830
Are you crazy?

551
00:36:58,420 --> 00:37:00,380
Searching in reverse
doesn't mean walking backward.

552
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:00,940
Shush.

553
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,730
If you're that good,
walk backward over this too.

554
00:37:14,650 --> 00:37:15,400
Seriously.

555
00:37:36,590 --> 00:37:37,760
You're stuck?

556
00:38:01,450 --> 00:38:03,180
The power of reverse thinking.

557
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,030
Not bad at all.

558
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,340
Is this what you called

559
00:38:29,750 --> 00:38:32,030
the Southern Archives?

560
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,790
Finally found it.

561
00:38:45,110 --> 00:38:46,040
What's going on?

562
00:39:15,770 --> 00:39:16,400
Careful!

563
00:40:23,740 --> 00:40:24,840
So magnificent.
